item.summary: Can't create fabric with 6.2.0.064 (Could not find quickstarts artefact)

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Kevin Earls Can you take a look at this one Kevin?
This issue also affects Fuse cartridge (failed to create new cartridge with the same error in logs).

I need to talk to Jon and then make a couple of build changes to fix this. In the meantime, the following workaround should take care of this:

1. Edit the file fabric/io.fabric8.import.profiles.properties; change "6.2.0.redhat-SNAPSHOT" to "6.2.0.redhat-064"
2. cd to the quickstarts directory, and build the quickstarts with the command: "mvn -Dtest=false -DfailIfNoTests=false --fail-never clean install. (The camel-cxf-contract-first build with fail. This is a known bug, see ENTESB-2624)
3. Start fuse.

If the workaround in the previous comment does not work, remove everything after the comma on the last line of fabric/io.fabric8.import.profiles.properties (i.e. this part: ",mvn:org.jboss.quickstarts.fuse/quickstarts-parent/6.2.0.redhat-SNAPSHOT/zip/profile}"

Hello Kevin,

both workarounds do work for me.
Upgrading to blocker as the workaround cannot be used for carts.

I have just checked in the workaround for this until I can resolve the other build issues

https://github.com/jboss-fuse/fuse/commit/c6d540ad1808f38059b5d0a1cbc1c953b329b064
What is blocking the fix for this? This is causing a lot of issues for QE so they would like to have fix in next tag (due Friday 20th).
I've just submitted a pull request with a fix.

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
1. unzip 6.2.0.064
2. start fuse (will result in ENTESB-2621)
3. fabric:create
